\par }{\b\insrsid14366951\charrsid4617661 Bodystorming
\par }{\insrsid14366951 \tab Often in the design process, it is necessary to have intimate knowledge of how the user interacts with the product. A good way to learn about this is for the designers to actually put themselves into the user\rquote 
s situation and be the user; really try it out. Bodystorming is a term for putting yourself in the user\rquote s position and actually using the thing that you are designing. 
Bodystorming can also be thought of as carrying out the design process being in the position of the user.
\par \tab Bodystorming is useful because it gives the designers a much more intimate knowledge of the context of their product. This is absolutely necessary, otherwise design decisions may have critical flaws }{\insrsid4617661 
that were never even considered until it is too late. For example, one of the factors that contributes to design is how natural it feels to use a product. Bodystorming can be very effective at teaching the designers how \'93natural\'94 or easy the product
 is to use.}{\insrsid14366951 
